{"id":14881825,"mediaExerciseId":"0b7ef1f7-1b40-4556-a478-9695ef5a8554","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612487,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":786,"solutions":[{"id":6004750,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will talk about how a swap contract is related to a forward contract.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A forward contract is a contract between two parties where they agree to buy or sell a certain product at a fixed time in the future. Generally, a swap is an agreement or contract between two parties where they exchange cash flows in an agreed upon time in the future. Basically, a swap is a series of forward contracts that have multiple fulfillment dates between two parties. \n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/88357277f66da614b832c79a6cea3c0f/58b7be27dd21e7424287904dfdef0778/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/88357277f66da614b832c79a6cea3c0f/58b7be27dd21e7424287904dfdef0778/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"One of the main risks of entering a swap with a swap dealer is the risk of default since the other party may not deliver the expected cash flow that was agreed upon in the contract. This is a huge risk since there is no standardization of the contract and there is no supervising body that can monitor this transaction. This means that the two parties in the swap contract, as well as the swap dealer, face risks. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":216,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/88357277f66da614b832c79a6cea3c0f/3624e83c8fd11a1da7c20db4e871cb3a/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/88357277f66da614b832c79a6cea3c0f/3624e83c8fd11a1da7c20db4e871cb3a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"5c9aab78-82e0-41e6-8303-cf4487de4b32","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881826,"exerciseName":"10","page":787,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"46ab8dc1-35c2-42d2-8b4e-94a952a5a209","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-critical-thinking-questions-10-46ab8dc1-35c2-42d2-8b4e-94a952a5a209"},{"id":14881827,"exerciseName":"11","page":787,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"8e7ac37c-8066-4880-b15e-df7828cd1b3b","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-critical-thinking-questions-11-8e7ac37c-8066-4880-b15e-df7828cd1b3b"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881824,"exerciseName":"8","page":786,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a2e0e651-892f-4c02-a9a6-35c509b77ac8","_webUrl":"htt